5:
Well? I imagine a sword of this quality 
should fetch a pretty penny.
6: How much would you pay for it?
9:
Hmm, I don't want to disappoint you, 
but this looks fairly old...
11:
An antique. It has history, and the 
blade is sharp as ever I have seen.
14:
It's in decent-ISH condition—for 
a collector's item—but no one would 
buy it for battle when there are 
cheaper modern options. *scribble* 
This is as high as I can go, sir.
17:
I see... I will try my luck elsewhere then. 
Thank you for your time.
20:
W-wait! You drive a hard bargain, sir. 
I can go a bit higher.
21:
I'll pay twice—no, THRICE the estimate 
I just gave you!
24:
Thrice? Yes, that should be enough to 
keep the study hall running for a while 
yet. You have a deal.
29:
That idiot calls himself a samurai? 
Hah! This's gotta be worth tens—
HUNDREDS of times what I paid!
30:
And now... now it's mine! Gwehaha, 
this is no ordinary blade, all right.
32:
I'll strip its power—like all the other 
demon blades I've collected... Then, 
finally, I will destroy the shogunate and 
conquer this land for myself!
35:
I am afraid I cannot lend my power to 
such a cause.
42:
Murakumo? Wh-who?
Where did you come from?!
45:
I was here the entire time, and heard 
everything. You are possessed by evil 
forces, and—
49:
I cannot allow the greed consuming 
you to spread!
64:
You did well yourself. 
That was some superb acting.
66:
I hardly have to act to look strapped 
for coin.
68: Ah, Alk! The mission was successful.
72: Is that guy gonna be okay?
76:
Yes, he should be safe now. I cut not 
his physical form—but the dark greed 
possessing him.
79:
I... *sniffle* I jusht wanded to b-b-
bring *hic* bring her back...
82:
If only I could do more. He will have to 
overcome his grief himself.
84:
You did more than enough already. 
His memories, at least, belong to him—
for good or ill.
87:
Thank you all for your cooperation. 
This case has given the Commission 
a great deal of trouble.
90:
The shogunate will no doubt be 
pleased to hear it's been resolved. 
Pleased enough to do the Commission 
a few favors, I hope.
95:
I only ask you treat this man with 
compassion. The curse plaguing him 
is gone—he will do no more harm.
98:
Of course. The magistrates won't be 
happy, but I can deal with them.
102:
One last thing. Why did you send me 
to Starview?
104:
Surely a diviner as capable as yourself 
could tell what I am.
105:
You could have curried the 
shogunate's favor if you had 
presented me to them instead. So 
why?
107:
I'll admit I considered giving you to 
them, but I'm better than that now.
109:
There's always another way—a way 
without sacrificing anyone. The two 
behind you helped teach me that.
114:
Ah, I see... Noble, indeed. I am proud to 
call you my partner, Alk!
117:
Nuh-uh, I hardly did anything when 
Orochi attacked!
120:
And always so humble! I am deeply 
grateful to have a place at your side.
124: I worry for your diviner friend, though.
127:
He has the makings of a great leader—
or terrible tyrant.
129:
It would have been interesting to 
adorn his hip, and see what name he 
carved into history for himself.
132:
Suizen has enough power of his own 
already.
134:
Yes, I can tell. He has something much 
greater than a blade.
136:
Friends.
...I wonder if I too may be counted 
among them. Ahahaha!
